---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Card from '@/components/Card.astro';
import BaseLink from '@/components/BaseLink.astro';
---
<BaseLayout 
    title="Building This Site: A Learning Journey"
    description="The technical evolution of this project, from its initial setup to iterative refinements in component design and user experience."
>
    <header class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-slate-100">A Living Project</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            This website is a practical case study in modern web development. This page documents its technical evolution, showcasing key architectural decisions and the process of iterative refinement for a better user experience.
        </p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-16">
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-6 dark:text-slate-200">1. Component Evolution: From Tabs to Scrollspy</h2>
            <p class="text-center text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                A key refinement was standardizing the site's layout. We replaced a fragmented, tab-based layout with a more cohesive single-page scroll experience, using the design from the "Ancient Math" page as the template for all content pages.
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="border border-red-300 dark:border-red-700 rounded-lg p-6 bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/30">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-800 dark:text-red-200">Old Method: Tabs & Accordions</h3>
                    <p class="text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 mt-2">The `f5-vpn` page originally used tab and accordion components. This hid content, requiring extra clicks and creating a disjointed user experience.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-green-300 dark:border-green-700 rounded-lg p-6 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/30">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-800 dark:text-green-200">New Method: Scrollspy & Cards</h3>
                    <p class="text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 mt-2">All content pages now use a single, flowing layout. A sticky "scrollspy" header navigates the user, while key information is presented in styled cards. This improves discoverability and creates a modern, consistent UX.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8 dark:text-slate-200">2. The Technology Stack</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-center">
                <Card icon="fa-solid fa-satellite-dish" title="Astro" blurb="The core of the site. Its 'Islands' architecture ensures fast performance by default, only loading JavaScript where needed." href="https://astro.build" isExternal={true} />
                <Card icon="fa-brands fa-react" title="React" blurb="For complex, stateful applications like the 'Ancient Math' designers, Astro seamlessly integrates React components as interactive islands." href="https://react.dev" isExternal={true} />
                <Card icon="fa-brands fa-github" title="GitHub Actions & Pages" blurb="The entire deployment process is automated. A push to the `main` branch triggers a build and deploys the static site to GitHub Pages." href="https://github.com/features/actions" isExternal={true} />
            </div>
        </section>

        <div class="text-center mt-12">
             <BaseLink 
                href="https://github.com/kairin/google-gemini-codes" 
                text="View Full Source on GitHub" 
                style="primary"
                isExternal={true}
                icon="fa-brands fa-github"
            />
        </div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
